@AndreyPavlenko this pull request solves at least 2 problems, and they are related to different backends.

Inner join bug for pandas backend should be fixed in a separate pull request. Reproducer can be found here: https://github.com/modin-project/modin/pull/5673#discussion_r1118173416. You can add it as a new test.

Let me know if you need help with this.

@LongnoseRob, please find attached my comments.
I have highlighted that log messages can be removed, since they are included in the parent's call.
I am not sure whether to recommend to call `super` at the beginning or at the end of the method, so I didn't comment about this, but may be other maintainers have some suggestion. Do you have any opinion about this?

This looks good to me.
Thanks @prabhat00155 for the good work.

@datumbox does my comment addresses your reservations?

@xiaohu2015 Thanks for the PR, LGTM!

Given that the code was modified heavily and it's not covered with tests, it would be good to do a run on our side to confirm that everything works as expected.

@prabhat00155 Let me know if you have the bandwidth for this.

@sallysyw Concerning the simplification discussed at https://github.com/pytorch/vision/pull/4874/files#r744539820, is this something you would be interested in doing or shall we create an issue about it?
